tion%20between%20Erez%20Druk%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Freed%20AI%2C%20an%20AI%20assistant%20for%20clinicians%2C%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Dr.%20Gabi%20Meckler%2C%20a%20family%20physician.%20This%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20and%20condensed%20for%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGabi%20Meckler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-school-regret-tried-please-parents-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresidency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20really%20began%20to%20feel%20the%20weight%20of%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20stay%20in%20the%20hospital%20until%20midnight%2C%20writing%20notes.%20You'd%20come%20home%20and%20still%20have%20notes%20to%20do.%20They%20were%20constant%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fact%20of%20life.%20Some%20people%20suffer.%20Some%20even%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20Erez%2C%20asked%20me%20what%20would%20make%20my%20life%20easier.%20I%20jokingly%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20just%20write%20my%20notes%20for%20me%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErez%20took%20the%20idea%20seriously.%20He%20started%20building%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EErez%20Druk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20built%20a%20simple%20proof%20of%20concept%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-gpt-custom-chatgpt-ai-15-minutes-guide-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20customizable%20version%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20few%20hours.%20It%20was%20a%20bare%20bones%20version%20of%20Freed%20that%20allowed%20for%20patient%20instructions%2C%20which%20are%20what%20clinicians%20send%20to%20patients%20post-visit%2C%20and%20subjective%20notes%2C%20which%20clinicians%20use%20to%20document%20patients'%20experience%20of%20their%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20showed%20it%20to%20Gabi.%20She%20said%20%26quot%3Binteresting%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20told%20me%20it%20still%20needed%20a%20few%20improvements.%20It%20would%20break%20at%20times%2C%20it%20didn't%20know%20the%20names%20of%20several%20medications%2C%20and%20wasn't%20attuned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-salary-how-much-doctors-earn-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edifferent%20specialities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20needed%20another%20data%20point%20beyond%20my%20wife%2C%20so%20I%20solicited%20the%20opinion%20of%20our%20friend%2C%20another%20clinician.%20She%20came%20over%20for%20dinner%2C%20I%20showed%20her%20the%20product%2C%20and%20her%20response%20was%20very%20different%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20immediate%20excitement.%20She%20texted%20the%20next%20day%20asking%20to%20use%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20we%20were%20on%20to%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20fast%20from%20there.%20It%20took%20some%20work%20to%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fwhat-is-hipaa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHIPAA%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompliant.%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20a%20beta%20version%20out%20quickly.%20We%20got%20some%20clinicians%20to%20test%20it.%20We%20asked%20them%20for%20feedback%20constantly.%20Building%20Freed%20isn't%20just%20about%20vision%20or%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20about%20listening%20to%20users%20and%20iterating%20based%20on%20what%20they%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeckler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20at%20a%20clinic%2C%20after%20residency%2C%20I%20began%20using%20Freed%20every%20day.%20I%20could%20finally%20finish%20my%20notes%20before%20leaving%20the%20office.%20One%20time%2C%20I%20forgot%20to%20send%20a%20referral%20for%20a%20patient%2C%20but%20Freed%20reminded%20me.%20That%20moment%20made%20me%20realize%20how%20much%20Freed%20was%20helping%2C%20not%20just%20with%20time%2C%20but%20with%20the%20details%20that%20I%20might%20have%20missed%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20doctors%20at%20the%20clinic%20noticed%2C%20too.%20They'd%20come%20to%20me%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20husband%3F%20He%20saved%20me%20hours%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%20That%20was%20rewarding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20love%20is%20that%20Erez%20takes%20my%20input%20seriously.%20He%20really%20understands%20the%20nuances%20that%20matter%20to%20clinicians%2C%20and%20the%20team%20is%20learning%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDruk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabi%20holds%20a%20weekly%20office%20hour%20with%20the%20product%20managers%20and%20designers%20where%20they%20share%20their%20work%20with%20her.%20She%20offers%20her%20perspective%20on%20what's%20useful%20and%20what%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20surprising%20%E2%80%94%20or%20maybe%20not%20%E2%80%94%20that%20even%20after%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20clinicians%2C%20there's%20always%20more%20to%20learn.%20We%20can%20never%20truly%20be%20in%20their%20shoes%2C%20there's%20a%20constant%20depth%20and%20nuance%20to%20uncover.%20That's%20why%20this%20setup%20is%20so%20valuable%3A%20It%20helps%20us%20get%20closer%20to%20understanding%20how%20they%20think%20and%20what's%20genuinely%20useful%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeckler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreed%2C%20as%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20is%20all%20about%20freedom.%20Our%20goal%20wasn't%20to%20tell%20clinicians%20how%20to%20use%20their%20time%20%E2%80%94%20we%20simply%20wanted%20to%20give%20it%20back%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20mindset%20really%20influences%20our%20marketing.%20We're%20very%20intentional%20about%20not%20telling%20clinicians%20what%20they%20should%20do%20%E2%80%94%20they%20know%20better%20than%20anyone%20else.%20We%20don't%20tell%20clinicians%20to%20be%20heroes%20or%20push%20messages%20like%20maintain%20%26quot%3Beye%20contact%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bspend%20more%20time%20with%20patients.%26quot%3B%20You%20probably%20already%20make%20enough%20eye%20contact.%20And%20if%20you%20want%20to%20Netflix%20and%20chill%2C%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20here%20to%20tell%20people%20how%20to%20be%20better%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDruk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManaging%20the%20relationship%20between%20husband%20and%20wife%2C%20founder%20and%20consumer%2C%20innovator%20and%20advisor%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20always%20easy.%20It's%20definitely%20annoying%20sometimes%20to%20get%20feedback%20that%20is%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeckler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20we%20do%20it%20well%2C%20though%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20we%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20be%20specific%20about%20feedback.%20Like%2C%20this%20is%20something%20you%20absolutely%20have%20to%20change%20before%20moving%20forward%2C%20versus%20this%20would%20be%20nice%2C%20or%20it's%20a%20bit%20iffy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20Erez%20that%20we%20needed%20to%20incorporate%20patient%20instructions.%20They%20include%20a%20summary%20of%20the%20visit%20and%20clear%20instructions%20based%20on%20the%20action%20plan%20created%20during%20the%20appointment.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20them%20easy%20for%20patients%20to%20read%2C%20understand%2C%20and%20follow.%20It's%20now%20one%20of%20the%20most%20loved%20features%20of%20Freed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20building%20a%20document%20analyzer%20now%20at%20the%20request%20of%20users.%20It%20will%20take%20any%20clinical%20document%20and%20give%20the%20clinician%20a%20summary.%20Users%20can%20also%20ask%20questions%2C%20and%20it%20will%20provide%20short%20responses%20with%20references%20from%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20whole%20time%2C%20since%20we%20launched%20in%20January%202023%2C%20Erez%20has%20been%20learning%20about%20medicine%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startup-unicorns-with-tiny-teams-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elearning%20about%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20I%20know%20he%20has%20to%20move%20fast.%20That's%20why%20I%20focus%20only%20on%20the%20most%20important%20things%2C%20and%20I%20push%20really%20hard%20when%20it%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20loved%20being%20involved%20as%20part%20of%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDruk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20is%20really%20my%20second%20obsession%20after%20Gabi%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I'm%20obsessed%20with%20work.%20So%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20can%20talk%20about%20everything%2C%20and%20she%20knows%20the%20people%20in%20the%20team%2C%20and%20what%20we're%20working%20on%2C%20is%20really%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20created%20Freed%20together.%20It's%20a%20love%20letter%20from%20us%2C%20our%20team%2C%20to%20all%20the%20clinicians%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreed-ai-doctor-notes-tool-founders-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747590785000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682922d6c6ad288d14814060%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreed-ai-doctor-notes-tool-founders-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tech%20entrepreneur%2C%20Erez%20Druk%2C%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Gabi%20Meckler%2C%20a%20family%20physician%2C%20built%20Freed%20AI%20to%20help%20doctors%20save%20time%20taking%20notes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40businessinsider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreed-ai-doctor-notes-tool-founders-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99m%20angry%20that%20I%20exist%2C%20the%20end%20goal%20is%E2%80%A6%E2%80%99%3A%20Chilling%20audio%20by%20Guy%20Edward%20Bartkus%20reveals%20true%20motive%20behind%20Palm%20Springs%20IVF%20clinic%20blast%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747590746000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-121253368%2Cimgsize-920006.cms%22%2C%22originID%22