m%2F681e4564a466d2b74ab58e4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223585%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%201910s%2C%20women%20sought%20out%20the%20advice%20of%20doctors%20and%20scientists%20at%20increased%20rates.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201910s%2C%20advancements%20in%20science%20and%20medicine%20brought%20a%20new%20focus%20on%20raising%20children.%20In%201914%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mchlibrary.org%2Fhistory%2Fchbu%2F3121-1914.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Labor%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0released%20a%20pamphlet%20outlining%20the%20best%20practices%20for%20infant%20care%2C%20from%20properly%20preparing%20a%20nursery%20to%20developing%20a%20feeding%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20also%20saw%20the%20rise%20in%20popularity%20of%20%26quot%3Bscientific%26quot%3B%20parenting%20advice%20from%20the%20emerging%20field%20of%20psychology%20and%20pedagogy%2C%20with%20figures%20like%20%3Cspan%3Epsychologist%20%3C%2Fspan%3EG.%20Stanley%20Hall%20giving%20advice%20to%20parents%20on%20how%20to%20best%20interact%20with%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%201911%20print%20of%20%26quot%3BA%20Handbook%20of%20Obstetric%20Nursing%20for%20Nurses%2C%20Students%20and%20Mothers%2C%26quot%3B%20new%20mothers%20were%20advised%20to%20avoid%20%26quot%3Bspoiling%26quot%3B%20their%20children%20into%20%26quot%3Blittle%20tyrants%26quot%3B%20by%20holding%20them%20for%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParenting%20styles%20during%20this%20time%20underwent%20a%20shift%20from%20the%20nurturing%2C%20motherly%20approach%20of%20the%201900s%20to%20a%20more%20authoritarian%20parenting%20structure%20that%20emphasized%20discipline%20in%20hopes%20of%20creating%20better-behaved%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHospital%20births%20became%20the%20norm%20by%201935%20in%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20infant%20mortality.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224599%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hospital%20nurse%20bringing%20newborn%20to%20mother.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e4548a466d2b74ab58e43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223806%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHospital%20births%20brought%20with%20them%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20challenges.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201900%2C%20nearly%20all%20births%20in%20the%20US%20occurred%20outside%20hospitals%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK201933%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Research%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20century%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20babies%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States%20were%20delivered%20by%20midwives%2C%20those%20numbers%20fell%20to%20about%2015%25%20by%201935%2C%20Margaret%20Marsh%2C%20a%20history%20professor%20at%20Rutgers%20University%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhyy.org%2Fsegments%2Fhow-did-birth-move-from-the-home-to-the-hospital-and-back-again%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR's%20WHYY%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20hospital%20deliveries%20became%20more%20common%20as%20women%20sought%20out%20the%20best%20medical%20resources%20they%20could%20attain%2C%20and%20by%201935%2C%20over%20half%20of%20births%20took%20place%20in%20a%20hospital%2C%20according%20to%20a%202008%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0014498307000241%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Explorations%20in%20Economic%20History%20journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20more%20mothers%20giving%20birth%20in%20hospitals%2C%20at%20first%20maternal%20mortality%20did%20not%20decrease%2C%20only%20dropping%20in%20the%201930s%2C%20the%202008%20paper%20reported%20%E2%80%94%20medical%20intervention%20during%20birth%20might%20have%20even%20increased%20fatalities%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20science%20of%20childbirth%20was%20still%20beginning%20to%20be%20understood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20efforts%20limited%20midwifery%20and%20pushed%20for%20hospital%20births%20during%20this%20time%2C%20and%20midwifery%20didn't%20become%20an%20organized%20field%20until%20the%201920s%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohsu.edu%2Fwomens-health%2Fbrief-history-midwifery-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOregon%20Health%20and%20Science%20University%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDuring%20World%20War%20II%2C%20the%20US%20government%20supplied%20universal%20childcare.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225525%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20at%20a%20daycare%20in%20the%201940s.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e44d8c6ad288d14808b27%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224075%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20wartime%20measure%20helped%20reduce%20the%20costs%20of%20day%20care%20for%20working%20mothers.%3Cp%3EDaily%20Herald%20Archive%2FSSPL%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20subsidized%20universal%20childcare%20through%20facilities%20that%20charged%20parents%2050%20to%2075%20cents%20per%20day%20per%20child%2C%20which%20would%20be%20from%20%249.81%20to%20%2414.71%20in%20today's%20money%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Farticles%2Funiversal-childcare-world-war-ii%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHistory.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initiative%20helped%20women%20join%20the%20workforce%20during%20the%20war%20when%20labor%20was%20most%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20help%20it%20provided%20mothers%2C%20the%20program%20ended%20in%201946%20after%20the%20war%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThroughout%20the%201950s%2C%20baby%20formula%20was%20advertised%20as%20the%20healthier%20option%20for%20babies.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223534%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Baby%20formula%20in%20the%201950s.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e44583fe8d39283657537%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222445%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiluting%20formula%20with%20evaporated%20milk%20got%20rid%20of%20concerns%20with%20the%20safety%20and%20freshness%20of%20feeding%20infants%20with%20cow's%20milk%2C%20which%20capped%20the%20popularity%20of%20formula-feeding%20in%20the%20past.%3Cp%3EChaloner%20Woods%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201950s%2C%20baby%20formulas%20were%20heavily%20popularized%20through%20advertisement%20campaigns%20and%20doctors'%20offices%2C%20which%20provided%20new%20mothers%20with%20samples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20some%20doctors%20began%20recommending%20that%20mothers%20use%20formula%20over%20breastmilk%20due%20to%20concerns%20with%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20breastmilk%20infants%20were%20getting%2C%20such%20as%20when%20the%20mothers%20were%20too%20stressed%20or%20tired%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aol.com%2Flifestyle%2Ffascinating-controversial-history-baby-formula-231353806.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYahoo%20Life%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20As%20women%20began%20entering%20the%20workforce%20in%20higher%20numbers%2C%20these%20concerns%2C%20along%20with%20the%20perceived%20flexibility%20of%20bottle-feeding%2C%20meant%20that%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20mothers%20didn't%20breastfeed%20their%20infants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201971%2C%20the%20breastfeeding%20rate%20in%20the%20US%20had%20reached%20an%20all-time%20low%2C%20with%2024%25%20of%20new%20mothers%20breastfeeding%20their%20newborns%20before%20being%20discharged%20from%20hospital%2C%20as%20reported%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC1448139%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2003%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Professor%20Wolf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBy%20the%201960s%2C%20more%20women%20had%20entered%20the%20workforce%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20two-career%20families%20and%20the%20need%20for%20childcare%20options.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224892%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20working%20in%20an%20office%20in%20the%201960s.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e47a73fe8d39283657618%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENearly%20half%20of%20the%20women%20in%20the%20US%20participated%20in%20the%20workforce%20by%201966.%3Cp%3EH.%20Armstrong%20Roberts%2FClassicStock%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20more%20women%20worked%20outside%20the%20home%2C%20with%20over%2040%25%20of%20women%20participating%20in%20the%20workforce%20by%201966%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcps%2Fdemographics%2Fwomen-labor-force.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20changing%20labor%20environment%2C%20new%20challenges%20to%20motherhood%20%E2%80%94%20and%20balancing%20home%20and%20work%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20also%20emerged%2C%20from%20feeding%20schedules%20with%20infants%20to%20a%20growing%20necessity%20for%20childcare%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20family%20dynamics%20began%20to%20shift%20from%20having%20one%20parent%20(usually%20the%20mother)%20stay%20at%20home%20to%20having%20two%20working%20parents%2C%20as%20reported%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebsco.com%2Fresearch-starters%2Fsocial-sciences-and-humanities%2Fstay-home-parenting-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20expanded%20childcare%20funding%20throughout%20the%20decade%20in%20response%20to%20the%20growing%20need%20for%20childcare%20options.%20In%201965%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Economic%20Opportunity%20launched%20Project%20Head%20Start%2C%20a%20summer%20program%20that%20provided%20low-income%20families%20with%20preschool%20instruction%20and%20support%20for%20children%20aged%203%20to%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Since%20then%2C%20the%20program%20has%20expanded%20beyond%20its%20initial%20time%20and%20age%20limitation%2C%20and%20in%202023%20over%20700%2C000%20children%20enrolled%20in%20preschool%20programs%20through%20Head%20Start%20and%20Early%20Head%20Start%2C%20according%20to%20the%20most%20recent%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fheadstart.gov%2Fprogram-data%2Farticle%2Fhead-start-program-facts-fiscal-year-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBreastfeeding%20rose%20in%20popularity%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20fueled%20by%20a%20feminist%20wave%20and%20controversies%20over%20baby%20formula%20marketing.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222657%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20breastfeeding%20baby.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e43c13fe8d39283657511%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221993%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDuring%20the%201970s%2C%20research%20began%20pointing%20to%20the%20unparalleled%20benefits%20of%20breastfeeding%20infants.%3Cp%3EJeff%20Goode%2FToronto%20Star%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20combination%20of%20more%20information%20about%20the%20effects%20of%20formula-feeding%20infants%20and%20a%20rising%20feminist%20movement%20that%20aimed%20to%20reclaim%20motherhood%20powered%20a%20resurgence%20of%20breastfeeding%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rise%20also%20coincided%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farchive.babymilkaction.org%2Fpdfs%2Fbabykiller.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboycott%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20baby%20formula%20producer%20Nestl%C3%A9%2C%20which%20the%20campaign%20accused%20of%20predatory%20marketing%20practices%20in%20countries%20in%20Latin%20America%20and%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20sued%20the%20publishers%20of%20the%20pamphlet%20promoting%20the%20boycott%20in%201974%2C%20with%20the%20publishers%20were%20found%20guilty%20of%20libel%20against%20the%20company%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1976%2F06%2F25%2Farchives%2Fnestle-wins-its-libel-suit-on-thirdworld-pamphlet.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20winning%20the%20case%20in%20the%20Swiss%20courts%2C%20the%20company%20was%20instructed%20to%20%26quot%3Breconsider%20its%20advertising%20policies%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20avoid%20being%20accused%20of%20immoral%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Judge%20J%C3%BCrg%20Sollberger%2C%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20over%20baby%20formula%20marketing%20led%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20to%20officially%20release%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20060324165724%2Fhttp%3A%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnutrition%2Fpublications%2Fcode_english.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguidelines%20for%20formula%20marketing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201981.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202001%2C%20the%20WHO%20had%20released%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.who.int%2Fgb%2Farchive%2Fpdf_files%2FWHA55%2Fea5515.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0lauding%20the%20nutritional%20value%20of%20breastmilk%20for%20infants%20and%20recommending%20that%20babies%20breastfeed%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months%20after%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAs%20women%20stayed%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20day-care%20services%20increased.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222572%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20at%20a%20day%20care%20center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e42b1c6ad288d14808a99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221633%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChildcare%20attendance%20rose%20in%20the%201980s%20as%20mothers%20entered%20the%20workforce.%3Cp%3EStar%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%2FStar%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%201970s%20and%201980s%2C%20increased%20female%20participation%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20which%20remained%20over%2050%25%20after%201978%2C%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20childcare%20options%20for%20parents%20of%20infants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rates%20of%20enrollment%20in%20childcare%20have%20steadily%20gone%20up%20since%20they%20began%20being%20measured%20in%201980%2C%20and%20by%201995%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20children%20between%20ages%203%20and%205%20in%20the%20US%20attended%20day%20care%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fprograms%2Fcoe%2Fpdf%2FIndicator_CFA%2Fcoe_cfa_2013_01.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESome%20working%20mothers%20began%20to%20receive%20paid%20maternity%20leave%20in%20the%20mid-1980s.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Working%20office%20woman%20in%20the%201990s.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e4153a466d2b74ab58d47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221061%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20fight%20for%20universal%20paid%20maternity%20leave%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20ongoing%20since%20the%201980s.%3Cp%3Eullstein%20bild%2Fullstein%20bild%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201984%2C%20discussions%20about%20paid%20maternity%20leave%20had%20begun%20entering%20the%20legislative%20government%2C%20but%20it%20took%20until%201993%20for%20Congress%20to%20pass%20the%20Family%20and%20Medical%20Leave%20Act%2C%20which%20provided%20some%20women%20and%20men%20with%20up%20to%2012%20weeks%20of%20unpaid%20leave%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oah.org%2Ftah%2Fnovember-3%2Fthe-history-of-family-leave-policies-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrganization%20of%20American%20Historians%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20measure%20limited%20the%20job%20protections%20to%20certain%20categories%20of%20workers%20meeting%20a%20set%20of%20guidelines%2C%20leaving%20about%2040%25%20of%20workers%20uncovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%2013%20states%20and%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20have%20enacted%20paid%20family%20leave%20laws%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbipartisanpolicy.org%2Fexplainer%2Fstate-paid-family-leave-laws-across-the-u-s%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBipartisan%20Policy%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20no%20national%20protections%20exist%20for%20paid%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDespite%20concerns%20about%20working%20mothers%2C%20studies%20showed%20that%20children%20were%20content.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20carrying%20baby.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e4091a466d2b74ab58d09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221819%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bmommy%20wars%26quot%3B%20between%20working%20and%20stay-at-home%20mothers%20reached%20a%20boiling%20point%20in%20the%201990s.%3Cp%3EMark%20Mainz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%201990s%2C%20debates%20between%20working%20and%20stay-at-home%20moms%20began%20dividing%20social%20spheres.%20These%20%26quot%3Bmommy%20wars%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20were%20called%20in%20a%201995%20opinion%20piece%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-srv%2Fnational%2Flongterm%2Fmommywars%2Fmommy.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20divided%20women%20as%20they%20navigated%20changes%20in%20the%20workforce%20and%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20mothers%20could%20be%20shamed%20for%20dividing%20their%20time%20and%20dedication%20between%20their%20work%20and%20their%20families.%20But%20in%202000%2C%20Ellen%20Galinsky's%20%26quot%3BAsk%20the%20Children%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20for%20which%20the%20author%20talked%20with%20over%201%2C000%20children%20of%20working%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20found%20kids%20did%20not%20wish%20for%20their%20parents%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20them%2C%20but%20for%20their%20parents%20to%20be%20less%20stressed%20and%20tired%2C%20as%20Galinsky%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Ffrontline%2Fwgbh%2Fpages%2Ffrontline%2Fshows%2Fteenbrain%2Finterviews%2Fgalinsky.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPBS%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aapd.org%2Fglobalassets%2Fmedia%2Fpublications%2Farchives%2Flong-26-02.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2004%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20pediatric%20dentists%20had%20reported%20a%20change%20in%20parenting%20techniques%2C%20with%20younger%20parents%20refraining%20from%20disciplining%20children%20in%20the%20ways%20that%20previous%20generations%20had%20and%20were%20more%20overprotective%20of%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWith%20the%20digital%20age%2C%20mothers%20began%20connecting%20online%20through%20mommy%20blogs.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225007%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mommy%20blogger%20with%20baby%20stroller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e4484a466d2b74ab58e0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BMommy%20blogs%26quot%3B%20gave%20women%20forums%20to%20discuss%20the%20difficult%20realities%20of%20motherhood.%3Cp%3EEdward%20Berthelot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%